-- Czech Telefonica shares fall to near PPF's buyout offer price
-- 
-- Thu May 22, 2014 03:10AM EDT
-- None



PRAGUE, May 22 (Reuters) - Shares in Telefonica Czech Republic <SPTT.PR> fell as much as 1.8 percent in early trade on Thursday, trading near the bid price of 295.15 crowns per share that was set in investment group PPF's mandatory buyout offer to minority shareholders.

At 0708 GMT, shares were down 1.6 percent at 295.00 crowns.